schools.name: Martin Luther King Jr Elementary School

data.description: Beautifully landscaped, iconic, historic plantation style home. All newly landscaped with outdoor lighting throughout, and updated zoned sprinkler system. Diving pool is salt water system with new pump, filter, ladder and step rail. Resurfaced with new tile border. Pool apron is cool decking. Newly renovated kitchen with large island, all new stainless steel appliances, quartzite countertops, subway tiles, undercabinet lighting, wet bar, hammered copper farmer's sink, and pot filler. Appliances to remain include an ice-maker, dishwasher, wine cooler, microwave, refrigerator, and range/oven. High ceilings all rooms. 3 LARGE bedrooms 15 x 23,14 x 16,13 x 15 and 2 baths up, lots of closet space. Livingroom 15 x 23 with fireplace, dining room 14 x 16, sunroom 14 x 18, paneled den 13 x 15 with french doors to 15 x 15 screened porch with ceramic tile floor (insulated for future enclosure). Roof - 40 year architectural shingles. Central air with additional central a/c unit for upstairs. Transferable Orkin termite contract and a 1 year homeowner warranty from American Home Shield. This house is rumored to be a Neil Reid, designed prior to his death for a planned community he was working on. Shirley Hills will remind you of Buckhead and Druid Hills in Atlanta as it was designed by landscape architect Frederick Law Olmstead.
